<item>
            <title>[LU-18746] &apos;lfs mirror extend&apos; should allow creating a new STALE mirror</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18746</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to allow &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend -N ... --no-resync&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to add a new mirror to a file that is marked &lt;tt&gt;STALE&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; resync&apos;d before the command returns.  This will allow the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; caller to specify the new mirror layout, but leave the task of copying the data into the mirror to another node (e.g. HSM agent or background scanning/resync tool).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
